<br>
I'm not one of those generally pro war people.  I hate the thought of war.  Even if you win war, the cost is so high that you don't really win.  Even if your side doesn't lose many lives, if the other side does, that is still a great loss.  Human beings are human beings wherever they live.<br>
<br>
I just don't see any alternatives.  After 12 years of diplomacy not working, I just have no reason to hope that it ever can.  I think Saddam has boxed the United States into a corner and war is the only option left.<br>
<br>
To think just how many lives have been needlessly lost since the beginning of time in wars... how much human effort has been wasted... how many great minds and talents lost.  The cost of war is staggering, I would love nothing more than a world in which there was never another war, and never need for one.  Sadly, we don't live in that world, and to be a strict pacifist means that those few evil people who are not strict pacifists will rule over all of us.  How sad though that such people must exist.<br>
